  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Patients with OSA receive manometry measurements with Apneagraph (AG) during one night of
      sleep. All patients are simultaneously evaluated with polysomnography. Patients who are not
      eligible for CPAP therapy are additionally studied with drug-induced sleep endoscopy (DISE).
      The frequency and obstructions patterns in different sleep stages are assessed. In addition
      obstruction patterns detected with AG are compared with DISE examination in the selected
      cases.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
